  "abstract": "Black root rot caused by Fusarium solani is considered a minor disease of chickpea.\r\nBut chickpea grown after rice has been observed during field visits to have this\r\nproblem more extensively and needs confirmation. A program of acquiring\r\nmicroorganisms (from natural sources, such as compost) with ability to suppress\r\nFusarium solani in plate culture was started at ICRISAT in 1997/98. A large number of\r\nbacteria assembled in 1998, was characterized in this study.\r\n",
